<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="154" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1229,1578]" pageId="3" pageNumber="154">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,510,1337,1362]" pageId="3" pageNumber="154">Distribution and habitat.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[523,779,1337,1362]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Alopoglossus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="3" pageNumber="154" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="buckleyi">
<emphasis box="[523,779,1337,1362]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="154">Alopoglossus buckleyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to western 
<taxonomicName box="[1069,1187,1337,1362]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Meliolaceae" genus="Amazonia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Meliolales" pageId="3" pageNumber="195" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Amazonia</taxonomicName>
, occurring in 
<collectingCountry box="[1360,1431,1337,1362]" name="Brazil" pageId="3" pageNumber="154">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,264,1373,1398]" name="Colombia" pageId="3" pageNumber="154">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[278,373,1373,1398]" name="Ecuador" pageId="3" pageNumber="154">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[436,488,1374,1397]" name="Peru" pageId="3" pageNumber="154">Peru</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[505,577,1373,1398]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1331,1353]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,413,1310]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,403,1315]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Distribution of examined material of Alopoglossus buckleyi and Ptychoglossus brevifrontalis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/581977/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="154">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry box="[633,704,1373,1398]" name="Brazil" pageId="3" pageNumber="154">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, it is known from the states of 
<collectingRegion box="[1069,1123,1374,1398]" country="Brazil" name="Acre" pageId="3" pageNumber="154">Acre</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bernarde" box="[1140,1379,1373,1398]" pageId="3" pageNumber="154" refString="Bernarde, P. S., Machado, R. A. &amp; Turci, L. C. B. (2011) Herpetofauna da area do Igarape Esperanca na Reserva Extrativista Riozinho da Liberdade, Acre - Brasil. Biota Neotropica, 11, 117 - 144." type="journal article" year="2011">
Bernarde 
<emphasis box="[1254,1306,1373,1398]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="154">et al</emphasis>
. 2011
</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingRegion box="[151,273,1410,1434]" country="Peru" name="Amazonas" pageId="3" pageNumber="154">Amazonas</collectingRegion>
. We could not verify the autencity of the record from 
<collectingRegion box="[879,936,1410,1434]" country="Brazil" name="Acre" pageId="3" pageNumber="154">Acre</collectingRegion>
, but the presence of 
<taxonomicName box="[1168,1292,1409,1434]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Alopoglossus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="3" pageNumber="154" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="buckleyi">
<emphasis box="[1168,1292,1409,1434]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="154">A. buckleyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[1329,1381,1410,1433]" name="Peru" pageId="3" pageNumber="154">Peru</collectingCountry>
near the border with the state of 
<collectingRegion box="[461,515,1446,1470]" country="Brazil" name="Acre" pageId="3" pageNumber="154">Acre</collectingRegion>
(
<collectingCountry box="[531,603,1445,1470]" name="Brazil" pageId="3" pageNumber="154">Brazil</collectingCountry>
) suggests a potential occurrence of this species in that state. 
<taxonomicName class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Alopoglossus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="3" pageNumber="154" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="buckleyi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="154">Alopoglossus buckleyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is terrestrial and diurnal, inhabits terra firme forests at high elevations (
<quantity box="[1079,1225,1482,1506]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.365" metricValueMax="1.83" metricValueMin="0.9" pageId="3" pageNumber="154" unit="m" value="1365.0" valueMax="1830.0" valueMin="900.0">900–1830 m</quantity>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Duellman" box="[1250,1431,1481,1506]" pageId="3" pageNumber="154" refString="Duellman, W. E. (1973) Descriptions of new lizards from the upper Amazon basin. Herpetologica, 29, 228 - 231." type="journal article" year="1973">Duellman 1973</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Avila-Pires" box="[151,346,1517,1542]" pageId="3" pageNumber="154" refString="Avila-Pires, T. C. S. (1995) Lizards of Brazilian Amazonia (Reptilia: Squamata). Zoologische Ferhandelingen, 299, 1 - 706." type="journal article" year="1995">Ávila-Pires 1995</bibRefCitation>
), but also open (semideciduous) forests with palms and bamboos at low elevations (
<bibRefCitation author="Bernarde" pageId="3" pageNumber="154" refString="Bernarde, P. S., Machado, R. A. &amp; Turci, L. C. B. (2011) Herpetofauna da area do Igarape Esperanca na Reserva Extrativista Riozinho da Liberdade, Acre - Brasil. Biota Neotropica, 11, 117 - 144." type="journal article" year="2011">
Bernarde 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="154">et al</emphasis>
. 2011
</bibRefCitation>
). It is mainly found among leaf litter, in shaded or partially shaded spots (
<bibRefCitation author="Avila-Pires" box="[1071,1267,1553,1578]" pageId="3" pageNumber="154" refString="Avila-Pires, T. C. S. (1995) Lizards of Brazilian Amazonia (Reptilia: Squamata). Zoologische Ferhandelingen, 299, 1 - 706." type="journal article" year="1995">Ávila-Pires 1995</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
